  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6602.06 sitting just below the massive +25.3B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher while providing strong support on dips toward the 6590 negative gamma pocket at -17.8B. The PIN regime with 41.4B total GEX creates a powerful mean-reversion dynamic, with the recent GEX surge indicating fresh hedging flows that should amplify the stabilizing behavior around current levels. Key inflection points are 6590 (dealer buying accelerates below) and 6605-6610 (heavy dealer selling above), with the 6619 flip strike acting as the upper boundary where regime dynamics shift.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong two-way action with dealers capping upside near 6605 and defending 6590 downside.",
